comment: Ok, wow, he actually used the term "Bacha Baazi," which is exactly what it's referred to as. One of the literal translations of this phrase means "Doing kinds," "Bacha" means kid, and "Baazi" means doing. It's not only common in Afghanistan but also in parts of Pakistan, where we're located, and other regions of South East Asia. Its an epidemic we are actively trying to mitigate and tackle here at Tomorrow's Journal. We're glad to see it brought to light on a platform as great as the JRE. Thank you, Joe Rogan.
